    "history" -> {"12", "13.3", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"Schur-Weyl duality", "quantum Schur transform"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "SchurBasis[n, d] constructs the Schur basis for a system of n particles \
each associated with a d-dimensional Hilbert space, i.e., \
(\\[DoubleStruckCapitalC]^d) \\[CircleTimes]n. SchurBasis[{q1, q2, ..., qn}] \
constructs the Schur basis for a composite system of labelled species {q1, \
q2, ..., qn}. The elements are expressed in terms of Ket[<|...|>] of species. \
SchurBasis[bs, d] or SchurBasis[bs, q] constructs a new Schur basis starting \
from already existing Schur basis bs by adding an unlabelled node of \
dimension d or a species q. SchurBasis[d] provides the operator form of \
SchurBasis.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "SchurBasis", 
    "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> 
    "SchurBasis", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
